IDOR - Access Control Checks:
Prevent Insecure Direct Object Reference by validating authorization on every resource access.

Dangerous:
@app.route('/api/user/<int:user_id>')
def get_user(user_id):
    # Returns any user's profile blindly
    return db.query(User).get(user_id)

Safe:
@app.route('/api/user/<int:user_id>')
def get_user(user_id):
    user = db.query(User).get(user_id)
    # Check if current logged-in user has permission to view this profile
    if current_user.id != user_id and current_user.role != 'admin':
        abort(403)
    return user

Also consider using unguessable identifiers (UUIDv4) instead of sequential integers.
